==English==
===Verb===
'''to strike out''', (past '''struck out''')

#{{intransitive}} to [[yield]] nothing
#: ''Dave '''struck out''' with the blonde.''
#{{intransitive}} {{baseball}} to be retired after three strikes
#: ''He '''struck out''' on a nasty slider.''
#{{transitive}} {{baseball}} to retire a [[batter]] after three [[strike]]s
#: ''He '''struck out''' Jones with a nasty slider.''

